body_fat$Density <- NULL

varlist <- colnames(body_fat)
varlist <- varlist[varlist != "BodyFat"]

1.3.0.1 Correlation Matrix of the Data

The heat map of the data



  par(cex=0.6,cex.main=0.85,cex.axis=0.7)
  cormat <- cor(trainingset[,varlist],method="pearson")
  cormat[is.na(cormat)] <- 0
  gplots::heatmap.2(abs(cormat),
                    trace = "none",
  #                  scale = "row",
                    mar = c(5,5),
                    col=rev(heat.colors(5)),
                    main = "Original Correlation",
                    cexRow = cexheat,
                    cexCol = cexheat,
                     srtCol=45,
                     srtRow=45,
                    key.title=NA,
                    key.xlab="|Pearson Correlation|",
                    xlab="Feature", ylab="Feature")

  diag(cormat) <- 0
  pander::pander(max(abs(cormat)))

1.4 Modeling body fat using raw set

fatmodel <- LASSO_1SE(BodyFat~.,trainingset);
predbfat <- predict(fatmodel,testingset)
pander::pander(fatmodel$coef)
(Intercept) Height Abdomen Wrist
-28.7 -0.0624 0.609 -0.208

1.5 Decorrelating using body fat as the outcome

trainfat_driven <- IDeA(trainingset,Outcome="BodyFat",thr=0.4)
testfat_driven <- predictDecorrelate(trainfat_driven,testingset)

1.6 Modeling body fat using decorrelated set

fatmodel_DE <- LASSO_1SE(BodyFat~.,trainfat_driven);
predbfat_DE <- predict(fatmodel_DE,testfat_driven)
pander::pander(fatmodel_DE$coef)
(Intercept) Age La_Weight Height La_Neck Abdomen La_Thigh La_Wrist
-25.3 0.0269 -0.0354 -0.0659 -0.263 0.614 0.211 -0.923 


devCoef <- fatmodel_DE$coef

coefnamesLa <- theLaFormulas[names(devCoef)]
coefnames <- coefnamesLa[!unlist(lapply(coefnamesLa,is.null))]
for (cn in names(coefnames))
{
  names(devCoef)[names(devCoef) %in% cn] <- coefnames[cn]
}
pander::pander(devCoef)
(Intercept) Age c(Age = 0.503675515652835, Weight = 1, Height = -1.20765947210019, Abdomen = -2.36287028227595) Height c(Age = -0.0354898686755508, Weight = -0.0704617706690604, Neck = 1, Abdomen = 0.00590032765907447) Abdomen c(Weight = -0.0835716449772485, Abdomen = 0.0947505063975145, Hip = -0.461395557529785, Thigh = 1) c(Neck = -0.229627614496331, Abdomen = -0.0174380468110068, Wrist = 1)
-25.3 0.0269 -0.0354 -0.0659 -0.263 0.614 0.211 -0.923 

obsCoef <- getObservedCoef(trainfat_driven,fatmodel_DE$coef)
pander::pander(obsCoef,"IDeA Modeling")
(Intercept) Age Weight Height Neck Abdomen Hip Thigh Wrist
-25.3 0.0184 -0.0345 -0.0231 -0.0509 0.732 -0.0975 0.211 -0.923 


pred2 <- as.matrix(testingset[,names(obsCoef[-1])]) %*% as.matrix(obsCoef[-1]) + obsCoef[1]
pander::pander(sum((pred2-predbfat_DE)^2))
